NAME
	send_datagram - send a message on the datagram channel

SYNOPSIS
	int send_datagram(string message)


DESCRIPTION
	Send a message on the datagram channel of a binary connection object.
	At least one message must have been received on the same channel
	before this function can be used.
	The return value is the length of the datagram sent if no error
	occurred, or 0 otherwise.

ERRORS
	An error will result if the current object has no datagram channel.

SEE ALSO
	kfun/query_ip_name, kfun/query_ip_number, kfun/send_message,
	kfun/this_user, kfun/users
